A chatbot is a computer program designed to simulate conversation with humans. It can understand user input (text or voice) and respond in a way that feels natural.

Key points:
Purpose: Help users get information, complete tasks, or have conversations.
Types:
Rule-based chatbots – follow predefined scripts.
AI-powered chatbots – use machine learning and natural language processing (NLP) to understand and respond more flexibly.
Uses:
Customer support
Virtual assistants
Education and tutoring
Entertainment and social interaction
How it works:
Takes input → processes language → finds meaning → generates a response

In short, a chatbot is a digital assistant that communicates with users automatically, making interactions faster and more convenient.
